com.revature.sms.domain

Class Token

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.revature.sms.domain.Token

  • @Entity
public class Token
extends java.lang.Object
    Object that represents the authorization Token. The token object will be used to track a user's session with an authentication token

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      private java.lang.String authToken
      String value that represents the primary key of the table, authToken is used to identify a specific Token object by it's unique value.
      private java.sql.Timestamp mostRecentAccess
      Timestamp object that represents the date that the token was last updated.
      private User user
      User value that represents the User object that's attached to this Token object.

    • Field Detail

      • authToken

        private java.lang.String authToken
        String value that represents the primary key of the table, authToken is used to identify a specific Token object by it's unique value.

      • mostRecentAccess

        private java.sql.Timestamp mostRecentAccess
        Timestamp object that represents the date that the token was last updated. This happens every time the user does something in the current session.

      • user

        private User user
        User value that represents the User object that's attached to this Token object. A single User can have multiple Token objects attached to it.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Token

        public Token(User user)
        Constructor that creates the Token object and initializes the User Instance variable based on the supplied user in the constructor. Also initializes the mostRecentAccess instance variable to the value of the current date and time that the object is created.
